excerpt: Outdoor water park with a large pool with several slides & waves, plus a shaded relaxation area.
detail_description: Aqualand Cap D'Agde is a sprawling 4-hectare outdoor water park that offers an array of aquatic attractions. The park features a large pool with thrilling slides and wave pools, providing entertainment for visitors of all ages. Additionally, the leisure island on the Mediterranean coast also includes other theme parks such as Europark and Captain Jako, offering various activities like kitesurfing, stand-up paddleboarding, sailing, and more.
name: Aqualand Cap D'Agde
address: Av. des Isles d'Amérique, 34300 Agde, France

excerpt: Seaside resort featuring beaches, a marina & the Musee de l'Ephebe, plus naturist areas.
detail_description: Cap d'Agde is a seaside resort known for its beaches, marina, and the Musee de l'Ephebe. It also has designated naturist areas, including a secluded village for nudists. Just a short drive away from Cap d'Agde is a 4-star campsite in Vias, making it an ideal base for exploring this famous resort in Herault.
name: Cap d'Agde

excerpt: Classic amusement park with funfair & thrill rides, food stands & a Western-themed restaurant.
detail_description: Luna Park Cap d'Agde is a popular amusement park that draws in numerous visitors. It features over twenty adult attractions, around twenty for children, and several dedicated to families, making it the ultimate amusement park. Spread across approximately 5 hectares, the park also offers various games of chance and skill. In addition to thrill rides and family-friendly attractions, Luna Park provides entertainment for all ages with its mini-golf course and nightclubs like Amnesia hosting renowned international DJs annually.
name: Luna Park Cap d'Agde
address: ÎLE DES LOISIRS, Av. du Passeur Challies, 34300 Le Cap d'Agde, France

detail_description: When visiting Agde, don't miss out on the diverse range of beach experiences it has to offer. One standout option is Plage De La Conque, a hidden gem with its unique black-sand beach located at the end of a volcanic trail originating from distant Auvergnes volcanoes. This secluded spot is ideal for a day visit and offers a different kind of coastal beauty.
name: Plage De La Conque
address: All. de la Conque, 34300 Agde, France

excerpt: Agde is a commune in the southern French department of Hérault. It is the Mediterranean port of the Canal du Midi. It is situated on an ancient basalt volcano, hence the name "Black Pearl of the Mediterranée". Wikipedia.
detail_description: Agde, a charming commune in Southern France, is known for being the Mediterranean port of the Canal du Midi. If you're planning a vacation in this seaside resort, Camping Resort Les Champs Blancs is an ideal choice for accommodation. Located in Cap d'Agde, this campsite offers a perfect base to explore the beautiful surroundings of Agde and enjoy all that Languedoc Roussillon has to offer in the South of France.
name: Agde

excerpt: Centuries-old fortress on a volcanic island, closed to the public but viewable on boat tours.
detail_description: Fort de Brescou is a centuries-old fortress situated on a volcanic island just off the Mediterranean coast near Cap d'Agde. Built in the 16th century, it served military and defensive purposes as well as housing political prisoners. Although not open to the public, visitors can view it on boat tours and learn about its fascinating history through guided tours. The surrounding area offers an underwater trail for exploring diverse marine life at shallow depths.
name: fort de Brescou

excerpt: Floating water park featuring inflatable structures including trampolines, slides & diving boards.
detail_description: AQUAPARK Cap d'Agde is a water park in Herault that offers an array of inflatable structures for visitors to enjoy. Located near camping Les Sablettes, this park provides entertainment for both adults and children aged 4 and above. From trampolines to slides, catapults, and climbing walls, there are plenty of activities to keep the whole family entertained. The park's giant inflatable water course also promises an adrenaline-pumping experience.
name: AQUAPARK Cap d'Agde
address: All. de Basse Terre, 34300 Cap d'Agde, France

detail_description: La Roquille is a beautiful beach in Cap d'Agde, offering a perfect spot for sunbathing, swimming, and leisurely walks along the shoreline. This family-friendly oasis provides plenty of space for relaxation and sandcastle building. The beach extends to the east and is conveniently located near a shopping center. Additionally, visitors can explore the nearby Brescou Island and its famous Brescou Fort.
name: La Roquille

detail_description: Mont Saint-Loup, a former volcano rising to 113m between Cap d'Agde and Agde, offers exceptional landscapes with contrasting colors, including islets, creeks, beaches, and cliffs. The eruption of this volcano 750,000 years ago gave the town of Agde its iridescent grey color and basalt monuments. A short hike from Cap d'Agde takes you to the summit of Mont Saint-Loup.
name: Mont Saint-Loup

detail_description: Mont Saint-Loup, located in Cap d'Agde, is a 113-meter high protected area that spans over 15 kilometers. Visitors can take a pleasant walk through the wild pine forest and observe the local flora and fauna including pines, holm oaks, almond trees, squirrels, birds, and butterflies. The shade provided by the large trees offers respite during hot periods. The highlight of the walk is the magnificent view of the Mediterranean Sea and Cap d'Agde.
name: Mont Saint-Loup

detail_description: Île des Loisirs is a popular destination in Agde, a lovely town in the Languedoc-Roussillon region of southern France. Positioned along the Mediterranean coast, Île des Loisirs is an energetic island offering various recreational activities and attractions suitable for families and thrill-seekers alike. Visitors can enjoy a fun fair that operates daily, catering to both young children and adrenaline enthusiasts.
name: Île des Loisirs

detail_description: The Ephèbe Museum, located in Cap d'Agde, Herault, France, is a unique establishment focused on the exploration and conservation of underwater archaeology. Since its establishment in 1984, the museum has amassed a diverse array of artifacts found in the sea, river, and Thau lagoon. These relics showcase Agde's strategic location at the confluence of various bodies of water.
name: Ephèbe Museum and underwater archeology
address: Av. des Hallebardes, 34300 Le Cap d'Agde, France

detail_description: Agde Cathedral, also known as St. Etienne Cathedral, is a remarkable 12th-century architectural marvel located in the picturesque town of Agde, France. The cathedral's imposing tower and fortress-like appearance with crenulations on its walls make it a striking sight to behold. Built with black volcanic basalt, the cathedral exudes a sense of strength and history. Visitors are captivated by the intricate stone carvings adorning its facade.
name: Agde Cathedral
address: 3 Rue Hôtel du Cheval Blanc, 34300 Agde, France

detail_description: Casino Barrière Cap d'Agde is a modern entertainment destination open daily from 10:00 AM to 4:00 AM, offering an array of gaming options. With over 6,300 cutting-edge slot machines and various table games like Blackjack, Roulette, Poker, and more, there's something for every gaming enthusiast. Electronic game fans can enjoy individual betting machines for electronic English Roulette.
name: Casino Barrière Cap d'Agde
address: rond point Carré D'As, 34300 Agde, France

excerpt: A traditional fishing village at the mouth of the River Hérault, Le Grau d’Agde is popular for its sandy beaches. Lively Quai Commandant Méric is lined with seafood restaurants, ice cream cafes, and souvenir shops, plus jetties for boat tours. Le Belvédère de la Criée fish auction house offers guided visits, while the Chapelle Notre Dame de l'Agenouillade contains a rock said to show an imprint of the Virgin Mary.
name: Le Grau d'Agde

detail_description: Bar Restaurant le Mississippi is a charming establishment located in the heart of Saint-Denis-d`Anjou. Housed in a beautiful building, it offers a delightful dining experience with a spacious restaurant area on the ground floor and comfortable hotel rooms on the first floor. The restaurant serves generous portions of pasta, fish, salads, grilled meats, and more while providing a magnificent view of the sea from its covered terrace.
name: Bar Restaurant le Mississippi

detail_description: Abyss Plongée is a top-notch diving center where the team's enthusiasm and professionalism create a welcoming and light-hearted atmosphere. The instructors are attentive, patient, and dedicated to building confidence in their divers. Whether it's completing training or simply going for dives, the experience is educational and enjoyable. The organization is excellent, ensuring a smooth and fulfilling diving experience. Divers can expect to learn a lot in just a few dives thanks to the expertise of the instructors at Abyss Plongée.
name: Abyss Plongée
address: 21 Imp. du Globe, 34300 le Cap d Agde, France

detail_description: PLAGE DE ROCHELONGUE, located in Languedoc-Occitanie, is a popular family holiday destination in the South of France. With over 75 years of history, it's considered one of the top 10 beaches in the region. The beach boasts pristine and clean golden sands, shallow waters perfect for swimming, and daily flag signals from lifeguard stations to ensure safe swimming conditions.
name: Plage de Rochelongue

detail_description: The tourist attraction Les Petits Trains du Cap d'Agde is a fun way to learn about the area's history and see some of the beautiful sights around Cap D'Agde. The guide/driver did an excellent job keeping everyone entertained during the ride.
name: Les Petits Trains du Cap d'Agde
address: Esplanade Pierre Racine Le Cap-d, 34300 Agde, France

detail_description: Captain Jako is a mini water park ideal for children under 12 years old, offered by Aqualand France. It features slides, water cannons, pirate ships, water swings, and many other attractions. The park entrance fee ranges from 10 to 15 euros depending on the entry times. Visitors have praised the quality of the welcome and well-maintained facilities with clear and clean water creating a lovely atmosphere thanks to the Director and his team of young people.
name: Captain Jako
address: se garer au parking gratuit, 10 passage du Soleil Levant, Rue du Gouverneur, 34300 Agde, France

detail_description: Cap d'Agde Studio Locations d'Appartements Village Naturiste is situated between Cap d'Agde and Agde, near the Mont Saint-Loup. The area boasts stunning beaches, crystal-clear waters, and a laid-back lifestyle that attracts tourists seeking the best of the Mediterranean. Additionally, there's a discreet village for nudists away from the modern resort. The studio is conveniently located near natural reserves and museums in the Naturist Village district.
name: Cap d'Agde Studio Locations d'Appartements Village Naturiste
address: 4 Av. de la Joliette, 34300 Cap d'Agde, France

detail_description: Golf Cap d'Agde, established in 2014, is located at the heart of Cap d'Agde and offers a refreshing green space amidst the surrounding apartment developments. The course features both an 18-hole and a 9-hole option, along with a driving range. Nestled in the Mediterranean landscape, it boasts undulating greens, strategically placed water hazards, and bunkers that provide a technical and diverse playing experience on the forested slopes of Mont Saint-Martin.
name: Golf Cap d'Agde
address: 4 Av. des Alizés, 34300 Le Cap d'Agde, France

detail_description: Plage Richelieu is a popular choice among the five main beaches in Cap d'Agde. It offers a nice beachside restaurant and bar, along with sweeping views of the bay down to Narbonne plage. The fine sandy beach extends towards le Grau d'Agde.
name: Plage Richelieu
Falaise
address: 2 Rue de la Falaise, 34300 Agde, France

detail_description: Aquarium Marin du Cap d'Agde is a must-visit attraction, especially on a rainy day. It's conveniently located near the port and offers an opportunity to explore the richness of marine life from around the world. The vibrant hues of aquatic plants and a variety of species in small but well-maintained tanks make it an enjoyable experience for both kids and adults. Additionally, visitors can delve deeper into their understanding of sea life through French signage provided throughout the establishment.
name: Aquarium Marin du Cap d'Agde
address: CAP d'AGDE, 11 Rue des 2 Frères, 34300 Agde, France

detail_description: Plage de la Roquille is a popular choice among the 5 main beaches in Cap d'Agde. It offers a nice beachside restaurant and bar with sweeping views of the bay down to Narbonne plage. The spacious parking lot, clean beach, and diverse crowd make it an enjoyable spot. There are relaxed beach bars offering a variety of drinks and food, without being noisy. During busy days, lifeguards are on duty for added safety.
name: Plage de la Roquille

detail_description: Rochelongue, a beloved destination in Languedoc, has been drawing visitors for over seven decades. Renowned as one of the top beaches in the region, it offers ample space for relaxation and enjoyment. The inviting beach bars create a perfect atmosphere to unwind during those warm summer days in southern France.
name: Languedoc

detail_description: Service d'Accueil du village naturiste is a large naturist village in Europe, established in 1950 with the OLTRA campsite. The area includes restaurants, a grocery store, shops, accommodations, camping facilities, and a beach. While check-in can be confusing and disorganized for non-French speakers, once settled in, it offers a great experience with beaches just minutes away. The site provides good facilities such as laundry services, dish-washing stations, showers and toilets.
name: Service d'Accueil du village naturiste

excerpt: Outdoor dinosaur-themed venue with 36 holes of mini golf, splash pads & trampolines, plus a cafe.
detail_description: Dino World Cap d'Agde, previously known as Dinoland, is an outdoor dinosaur-themed venue offering a variety of activities for all ages. The park features realistic dinosaur figures with informative plaques, a themed 36-hole mini-golf course, trampolines, and splash pads. It consists of three amusement parks: Dinopark, Dinogolf, and Dino Aquadino spread across 13,000 square meters near Marseillan and Vias.
name: Dino World Cap d'Agde
address: Ile des Loisirs, 28 Av. du Passeur Challies, 34300 Le Cap d'Agde, France

excerpt: Tube slides, splash pools & water obstacles around a model pirate ship, plus casual outdoor dining.
detail_description: Pirate Cove is a wonderful aquatic amusement park designed for younger kids, featuring tube slides, water obstacles, and splash pools surrounding a model pirate ship. In addition to the exciting water attractions, there are also casual outdoor dining options available. The rides in this park are suitable for all ages and offer amazing experiences that everyone can enjoy. Overall, Pirate Cove is an incredible destination for families looking to have fun in the sun with plenty of water-based activities to keep everyone entertained.
name: Pirate Cove

excerpt: This popular, sandy city beach offers swimming & sunbathing, plus nearby shops & eateries.
name: Le Môle

detail_description: La Roquille beach is a beautiful location that offers pleasant opportunities for strolling, unwinding, and cycling. The area boasts exceptional vistas and provides an ideal setting for sunbathing, swimming, and rejuvenation.
name: La Roquille

detail_description: The Grande Roue du Cap d'Agde is a remarkable tourist attraction located in the coastal resort town of Cap d'Agde. Standing tall at 60 meters and equipped with 36 six-seater cabins, it offers visitors an awe-inspiring aerial view of the entire resort and its magnificent shoreline facing the Mediterranean Sea. This ferris wheel is undoubtedly one of the most scenic ways to appreciate the stunning beauty of Cap d'Agde from above.
name: Grande Roue du Cap d'Agde
address: 22 Rue de la Gabelle, 34300 Agde, France

detail_description: The first time trying out jet skiing at Aloha Jet was an amazing adventure. The instructor, Thomas, provided clear instructions and instilled confidence in us. He was a great teacher who took the time to answer our questions. The schedules were adhered to and the discovery trail offered breathtaking scenery. We had the freedom to go at our own pace, whether it be fast or slow. These unforgettable memories have left us excited for more adventures with Aloha Jet in the future!
name: Aloha Jet
address: Av. du Rec de l'Entrée, 11370 Leucate, France

excerpt: Open seasonally, this long-running pirate-themed amusement park offers rides, games & snack stands.
detail_description: Pirat'Parc is a seasonal amusement park with a pirate theme, offering various rides, games, and food stands. It has been entertaining visitors for a long time. Many people, including teenagers like my son, enjoy visiting this park during their visits to their grandparents. They particularly look forward to trying out the new adult rides that are more thrilling and physically challenging. Purchasing a pass is cost-effective because it allows unlimited access over multiple years based on age and height restrictions.
name: Pirat'Parc

detail_description: Lasjump is a water park that features a variety of activities such as blobbing and jumping. It's filled with lots of fun for everyone who visits.
name: L'As jump Blob jump et snack
address: All. de Basse Terre, 34300 Cap d' Agde, France

detail_description: La Pointe du Cap d'Agde is a must-visit observation point with stunning views of black sand beaches, cliffs, and a clear sea. It's an ideal spot for a serene solo walk or to share the magic with fellow travelers. Families will enjoy the diverse marine life at the Cap d'Agde aquarium, which offers practical and playful explanations about its many species. The area also features picturesque landscapes and panoramic views, although some buildings nearby slightly detract from its natural beauty.
name: La Pointe du Cap- d'Agde

detail_description: Water Jump Cap d'Agde is a thrilling water attraction that offers an hour of fun with various levels of sensations. It provides a unique experience, especially for those visiting from Italy, as it features the highest slide at three meters and exciting diving opportunities. The lifeguard ensures safety, making it suitable for families with children. Visitors can leave their belongings in the cabin and enjoy the right temperature of the water while experiencing different levels of excitement.
name: Water Jump Cap d'agde
address: Île des Loisirs, All. de Basse Terre, 34300 Agde, France

name: Galerie Naja
address: Cap d'Agde (Le, 78 All. de la Flânerie, 34300 Agde, France
